SQL Server Management Studio
1. Create a database in SQL and name it midterm db. (5 points)
2. Inside of the your database create the following tables as shown in below figure. Note that the key icon shown in below diagram stands for primary key. (45 points)
3. Insert five random records into each table. (15 points)
4. Implement one stored procedure for each table and they should delete a specific record according to the given id. (55 points)
5. Implement one trigger for the Product table and it should get invoked when the user updates any record into this table. (40 points)
